{"title_page": "Algeti National Park", "text_new": "{{Infobox protected area\n| name =  Algeti National Park\n| iucn_category = II\n| photo = Algeti Lake.jpg\n| photo_caption = Landscape around the Algeti reservoir\n| map = Georgia#Georgia Kvemo Kartli\n| relief = 1\n| location = {{flag|Georgia}}\n| nearest_city = [[Manglisi]]\n| coordinates = {{coords|41|43|N|44|19|E|display=inline, title}}\n| area_km2 =157.63\n| area_ref = <ref name=\"protectedplanet\" />\n| established = 2007\n| visitation_num = 8,030\n| visitation_year = 2015\n| governing_body = Agency of Protected Areas\n| website =[http://apa.gov.ge/en/protected-areas/cattestone/algeTis-erovnuli-parki Algeti National Park]\n}}\nThe '''Algeti National Park''' ({{lang-ka|\u10d0\u10da\u10d2\u10d4\u10d7\u10d8\u10e1 \u10d4\u10e0\u10dd\u10d5\u10dc\u10e3\u10da\u10d8 \u10de\u10d0\u10e0\u10d9\u10d8}}, ''algetis erovnuli parki'') is a [[List of protected areas of Georgia|protected area]] in [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]], in the southeast of the country.<ref name=\"protectedplanet\">[https://www.protectedplanet.net/algeti-national-park Algeti in Georgia] ''Protected Planet''</ref><ref>[http://sppa-georgia.org/sppa/index.php/en/about-the-programme/general/78-sppa/97-algeti Algeti] Support Programme for Protected Areas in the Caucasus - Georgia (SPPA-Georgia).</ref>\nIt lies in the [[mkhare|region]] of [[Kvemo Kartli]], within the [[Municipality of Tetritsqaro]], some 60&nbsp;km southwest of the nation's capital, [[Tbilisi]].\n\nThe Algeti National Park stretches along the upper [[Algeti valley]] at the woody southern slopes of the eastern [[Trialeti Range]], with the highest point being [[Kldekari (mountain)|Mount Kldekari]] at 2,000 m above sea level. The park was founded under the [[Georgian SSR|Soviet government]] in 1965 as a state reserve to protect the easternmost limits of the [[Caucasian Spruce]] and [[Nordmann Fir]]. In 2007, it was reorganized into a national park.<ref>[http://www.dpa.gov.ge/index.php?site-id=5&page=1&id=221 Algeti National Park] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721030207/http://www.dpa.gov.ge/index.php?site-id=5&page=1&id=221 |date=2011-07-21 }}. Agency of Protected Areas of Georgia. Retrieved on January 7, 2010</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Dashbashi Canyon Natural Monument]]\n*[[Birtvisi]]\n*[[Manglisi Cathedral]]\n\n== References ==\n{{commons category|Algeti National Park}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Protected areas of Georgia (country)}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:National parks of Georgia (country)]]\n[[Category:Protected areas established in 1965]]\n[[Category:Geography of Kvemo Kartli]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Kvemo Kartli]]\n\n\n{{Georgia-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox protected area\n| name =  Algeti National Park\n| iucn_category = II\n| photo = Algeti Lake.jpg\n| photo_caption = Landscape around the Algeti reservoir\n| map = Georgia#Georgia Kvemo Kartli\n| relief = 1\n| location = {{flag|Georgia}}\n| nearest_city = [[Manglisi]]\n| coordinates = {{coords|41|43|N|44|19|E|display=inline, title}}\n| area_km2 =157.63\n| area_ref = <ref name=\"protectedplanet\" />\n| established = 2007\n| visitation_num = 8,030\n| visitation_year = 2015\n| governing_body = Agency of Protected Areas\n| website =[http://apa.gov.ge/en/protected-areas/cattestone/algeTis-erovnuli-parki Algeti National Park]\n}}\nThe '''Algeti National Park''' ({{lang-ka|\u10d0\u10da\u10d2\u10d4\u10d7\u10d8\u10e1 \u10d4\u10e0\u10dd\u10d5\u10dc\u10e3\u10da\u10d8 \u10de\u10d0\u10e0\u10d9\u10d8}}, ''algetis erovnuli parki'') is a [[List of protected areas of Georgia|protected area]] in [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]], in the southeast of the country.<ref name=\"protectedplanet\">[https://www.protectedplanet.net/algeti-national-park Algeti in Georgia] ''Protected Planet'' </ref><ref>[http://sppa-georgia.org/sppa/index.php/en/about-the-programme/general/78-sppa/97-algeti Algeti] Support Programme for Protected Areas in the Caucasus - Georgia (SPPA-Georgia).</ref>\nIt lies in the [[mkhare|region]] of [[Kvemo Kartli]], within the [[Municipality of Tetritsqaro]], some 60 km southwest of the nation's capital, [[Tbilisi]].  \n\nThe Algeti National Park stretches along the upper [[Algeti valley]] at the woody southern slopes of the eastern [[Trialeti Range]], with the highest point being [[Kldekari (mountain)|Mount Kldekari]] at 2,000 m above sea level. The park was founded under the [[Georgian SSR|Soviet government]] in 1965 as a state reserve to protect the easternmost limits of the [[Caucasian Spruce]] and [[Nordmann Fir]]. In 2007, it was reorganized into a national park.<ref>[http://www.dpa.gov.ge/index.php?site-id=5&page=1&id=221 Algeti National Park] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721030207/http://www.dpa.gov.ge/index.php?site-id=5&page=1&id=221 |date=2011-07-21 }}. Agency of Protected Areas of Georgia. Retrieved on January 7, 2010</ref>\n== See also ==\n*[[Dashbashi Canyon Natural Monument]]\n*[[Birtvisi]]\n*[[Manglisi Cathedral]]\n\n== References ==\n{{commonscat|Algeti National Park}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Protected areas of Georgia (country)}}\n\n[[Category:National parks of Georgia (country)]]\n[[Category:Protected areas established in 1965]]\n[[Category:Geography of Kvemo Kartli]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Kvemo Kartli]]\n\n\n{{Georgia-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algeti_National_Park"}
{"title_page": "Mork & Mindy/Laverne & Shirley/Fonz Hour", "text_new": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name = Mork & Mindy / Laverne & Shirley / Fonz Hour\n| genre = [[Cartoon series]]\n| director = [[George Gordon (animator)|George Gordon]]<br>Bob Hathcock<br>John Kimball<br>[[Rudy Larriva]]<br> [[Carl Urbano]]<br> [[Rudy Zamora]]\n| starring =[[Robin Williams]]<br>[[Pam Dawber]]<br>[[Conrad Janis]]<br>[[Henry Winkler]]\n| voices = [[Ralph James]]<br>[[Stan Jones (actor)|Stan Jones]]<br>[[Ron Palillo]]<br>[[Lynne Marie Stewart]]<br>[[Frank Welker]]<br>[[Shavar Ross]]<br>Mark L. Taylor \n| composer = [[Hoyt Curtin]]\n| country = USA\n| language = English\n| num_seasons = 1\n| num_episodes = 27\n| executive_producer = [[William Hanna]]<br>[[Joseph Barbera]]<br>Joe Ruby<br>Ken Spears\n| producer = Joe Ruby<br> Art Scott<br> Ken Spears\n| runtime = 1 hour\n| company = [[Hanna-Barbera|Hanna-Barbera Productions]]<br> [[Ruby-Spears|Ruby-Spears Enterprises]]<br> [[Paramount Television (original)|Paramount Television]]\n| distributor = \n| channel = [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n| first_aired = {{Start date|1982|9|25}}\n| last_aired = {{End date|1983|9|3}}\n| preceded_by = ''[[The Fonz and the Happy Days Gang]]''<br>''[[Laverne & Shirley (1981 TV series)|Laverne & Shirley in the Army]]''\n| related = ''[[Mork & Mindy]]''<br> ''[[Laverne & Shirley]]''<br> ''[[Happy Days]]''\n}}\n'''''Mork & Mindy/Laverne & Shirley/Fonz Hour''''' is a 1982-1983 American [[Saturday-morning cartoon|animated television series]] produced by [[Hanna-Barbera|Hanna-Barbera Productions]] and [[Ruby-Spears|Ruby-Spears Enterprises]] in association with [[Paramount Television (original)|Paramount Television]], featuring animated versions of characters from the live-action sitcoms ''[[Mork & Mindy]]'', ''[[Laverne & Shirley]]'' and ''[[Happy Days]]'', all part of the same franchise. This [[Saturday morning cartoon|Saturday morning]] series lasted for one season on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]].<ref name=Daytime>{{cite book |last1=Hyatt |first1=Wesley |title=The Encyclopedia of Daytime Television |date=1997 |publisher=Watson-Guptill Publications |isbn=978-0823083152 |url=https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaofda00hyat/page/256/mode/2up|accessdate=19 March 2020|page=257}}</ref>\n\nThis show was divided into two segments: ''Mork & Mindy'' and ''Laverne & Shirley with The Fonz''. The ''Laverne & Shirley'' half-hour was the second season of ''[[Laverne & Shirley (1981 TV series)|Laverne & Shirley in the Army]]'', with the addition of [[Fonzie|The Fonz]] and his dog Mr. Cool from the earlier cartoon ''[[The Fonz and the Happy Days Gang]]''.<ref name=Perlmutter>{{cite book |last1=Perlmutter |first1=David |title=The Encyclopedia of American Animated Television Shows |date=2018 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1538103739 |page=352}}</ref>\n\n==''Mork & Mindy''==\nIn the ''Mork & Mindy'' segment, in which [[Robin Williams]] and [[Pam Dawber]] voiced the title characters, a teenaged Mork is sent to Earth from planet Ork to observe the lives of human teenagers and enroll in a local school. As on the original show, Mindy McConnell and her father Fred (voiced by [[Conrad Janis]]) are the only Earthlings who know that he is an alien and he sends telepathic reports of his experiences to Orkan ruler Orson (voiced by an uncredited [[Ralph James]]). Unlike the original show, Mork is accompanied by his Orkan pet, a pink, six-legged, [[dog]]-like creature named Doing (voiced by [[Frank Welker]]) which is pronounced as \"Doyng\". Other characters in the show included Eugene (voiced by [[Shavar Ross]]), Hamilton (voiced by Mark L. Taylor), and Principal Caruthers (voiced by an uncredited [[Stan Jones (actor)|Stanley Jones]]).\n\n===Episode list===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"background:#ffffff\"\n|- style=\"color:#ffffff\"\n! style=\"background:#B11030; width:30px\"| N\u00ba\n! style=\"background:#B11030\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#B11030; width:135px\"| Or