e|1982|12|11}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M14\n| Title = Muddle in the Huddle\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|12|18}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M15\n| Title = The Incredible Shrinking Mork\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|12|25}}\n| ShortSummary = In an effort to retrieve Mork's watch stolen from a rat, Mork, Mindy and Doing shrink using a special device.\n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M16\n| Title = The Invisible Mork\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|1|8}}\n| ShortSummary = Mork drinks strawberry juice that makes him invisible, then takes advantage of his invisibility by trying to fight a bully to win Mindy's affections.\n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M17\n| Title = The Fluke Spook\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|1|15}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M18\n| Title = Mayhem for the Mayor\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|1|22}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M19\n| Title = Coo Coo Caveboy\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|1|29}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M20\n| Title = A Treasure Ain't No Pleasure\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|2|5}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M21\n| Title = The Mork with the Midas Touch\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|2|12}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M22\n| Title = Extra Terrestrial Toddler\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|2|19}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M23\n| Title = Time Slipper Slip-Up\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|2|26}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M24\n| Title = Super Mork\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|3|5}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M25\n| Title = Mork P.I.\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|3|12}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M26\n| Title = Monkey on My Back Pack\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|3|19}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M27\n| Title = On Your Mork, Get Set, Go!\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983||}}\n| ShortSummary = This episode was pre-empted on January 1, 1983 due to coverage of the Tournament of Roses Parade. The exact date this episode was shown, if at all, is uncertain.\n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n|}\n\n===Cast===\n* [[Robin Williams]] - Mork\n* [[Pam Dawber]] - Mindy McConnell\n* [[Conrad Janis]] - Frederick McConnell\n* [[Ralph James]] - Orson\n* [[Stan Jones (actor)|Stan Jones]] - Principal Caruthers\n* [[Shavar Ross]] - Eugene\n* Mark L. Taylor - Hamilton\n* [[Frank Welker]] - Doing\n* [[Dennis Alwood]]\n* [[Jack Angel]]\n* [[Dave Coulier]]\n* [[Julie McWhirter|Julie McWhirter Dees]]\n* [[Alan Dinehart III|Alan Dinehart]]\n* [[Walker Edmiston]]\n* [[Stan Freberg]]\n* [[Bob Holt (actor)|Bob Holt]]\n* [[Katie Leigh|Katherine Leigh]]\n* [[Kenneth Mars]]\n* [[Allan Melvin]]\n* [[Sidney Miller (actor)|Sidney Miller]]\n* [[Neil Ross]]\n* [[Michael Rye]]\n* [[Steve Schatzberg]]\n* [[Marilyn Schreffler]]\n* [[Steve J. Spears|Steve Spears]]\n* [[Larry Storch]]\n* [[Alan Young]]\n\n==''Laverne & Shirley with The Fonz''==\nThis segment is a continuation of ''[[Laverne & Shirley (1981 TV series)|Laverne & Shirley in the Army]]'', the only difference being the addition of [[Fonzie|The Fonz]] (voiced by [[Henry Winkler]]) and his dog Mr. Cool (from ''[[The Fonz and the Happy Days Gang]]''; voiced by [[Frank Welker]]) as mechanics in the army camp's [[fleet vehicle|motor pool]]. [[Cindy Williams]] quit her role as Shirley on the live-action sitcom ''[[Laverne & Shirley]]'' in August 1982. Conversely, Williams' role in the animated series was taken over by friend [[Lynne Marie Stewart]]. Only eight episodes were produced. Thus, the existing segments produced up to that point were rerun for the rest of the series. Except for a few publicity cel paintings, no further plans for the series were made.{{citation needed|date=March 2015}}\n\n===Episode list===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"background:#ffffff\"\n|- style=\"color:#ffffff\"\n! style=\"background:#006400; width:20px\"| N\u00ba\n! style=\"background:#006400\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#006400; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = L1\n| Title = The Speed Demon Get-Away Caper\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|9|25}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 006400\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = L2\n| Title = Swamp Monsters Speak with Forked Face\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|2}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 006400\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = L3\n| Title = Movie Madness\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|9}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 006400\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = L4\n| Title = One Million Laughs B.C.\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|16}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 006400\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = L5\n| Title = The Robot Recruit\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|23}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 006400\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = L6\n| Title = All the President's Girls\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|30}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 006400\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = L7\n| Title = Laverne and Shirley and the Beanstalk\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|11|6}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 006400\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = L8\n| Title = Raiders of the Lost Pork\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|11|13}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = 006400\n}}\n|}