American children's animated fantasy television series]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name = Mork & Mindy / Laverne & Shirley / Fonz Hour\n| genre = [[Cartoon series]]\n| director = [[George Gordon (animator)|George Gordon]]<br>Bob Hathcock<br>John Kimball<br>[[Rudy Larriva]]<br> [[Carl Urbano]]<br> [[Rudy Zamora]]\n| starring =[[Robin Williams]]<br>[[Pam Dawber]]<br>[[Conrad Janis]]<br>[[Henry Winkler]]\n| voices = [[Ralph James]]<br>[[Stan Jones (actor)|Stan Jones]]<br>[[Ron Palillo]]<br>[[Lynne Marie Stewart]]<br>[[Frank Welker]]<br>[[Shavar Ross]]<br>Mark L. Taylor \n| composer = [[Hoyt Curtin]]\n| country = USA\n| language = English\n| num_seasons = 1\n| num_episodes = 27\n| executive_producer = [[William Hanna]]<br>[[Joseph Barbera]]<br>Joe Ruby<br>Ken Spears\n| producer = Joe Ruby<br> Art Scott<br> Ken Spears\n| runtime = 1 hour\n| company = [[Hanna-Barbera|Hanna-Barbera Productions]]<br> [[Ruby-Spears|Ruby-Spears Enterprises]]<br> [[Paramount Television (original)|Paramount Television]]\n| distributor = \n| channel = [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n| first_aired = {{Start date|1982|9|25}}\n| last_aired = {{End date|1983|9|3}}\n| preceded_by = ''[[The Fonz and the Happy Days Gang]]''<br>''[[Laverne & Shirley (1981 TV series)|Laverne & Shirley in the Army]]''\n| related = ''[[Mork & Mindy]]''<br> ''[[Laverne & Shirley]]''<br> ''[[Happy Days]]''\n}}\n'''''Mork & Mindy/Laverne & Shirley/Fonz Hour''''' is a 1982-1983 American [[Saturday-morning cartoon|animated television series]] produced by [[Hanna-Barbera|Hanna-Barbera Productions]] and [[Ruby-Spears|Ruby-Spears Enterprises]] in association with [[Paramount Television (original)|Paramount Television]], featuring animated versions of characters from the live-action sitcoms ''[[Mork & Mindy]]'', ''[[Laverne & Shirley]]'' and ''[[Happy Days]]'', all part of the same franchise. This [[Saturday morning cartoon|Saturday morning]] series lasted for one season on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]].<ref name=Daytime>{{cite book |last1=Hyatt |first1=Wesley |title=The Encyclopedia of Daytime Television |date=1997 |publisher=Watson-Guptill Publications |isbn=978-0823083152 |url=https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaofda00hyat/page/256/mode/2up|accessdate=19 March 2020|page=257}}</ref>\n\nThis show was divided into two segments: ''Mork & Mindy'' and ''Laverne & Shirley with The Fonz''. The ''Laverne & Shirley'' half-hour was the second season of ''[[Laverne & Shirley (1981 TV series)|Laverne & Shirley in the Army]]'', with the addition of [[the Fonz]] and his dog Mr. Cool from the earlier cartoon ''[[The Fonz and the Happy Days Gang]]''.<ref name=Perlmutter>{{cite book |last1=Perlmutter |first1=David |title=The Encyclopedia of American Animated Television Shows |date=2018 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1538103739 |page=352}}</ref>\n\n==''Mork & Mindy''==\nIn the ''Mork & Mindy'' segment, in which [[Robin Williams]] and [[Pam Dawber]] voiced the title characters, a teenaged Mork is sent to Earth from planet Ork to observe the lives of human teenagers and enroll in a local school. As on the original show, Mindy McConnell and her father Fred (voiced by [[Conrad Janis]]) are the only Earthlings who know that he is an alien and he sends telepathic reports of his experiences to Orkan ruler Orson (voiced by an uncredited [[Ralph James]]). Unlike the original show, Mork is accompanied by his Orkan pet, a pink, six-legged, [[dog]]-like creature named Doing (voiced by [[Frank Welker]]) which is pronounced as \"Doyng\". Other characters in the show included Eugene (voiced by [[Shavar Ross]]), Hamilton (voiced by Mark L. Taylor), and Principal Caruthers (voiced by an uncredited [[Stan Jones (actor)|Stanley Jones]]).\n\n===Episode list===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"background:#ffffff\"\n|- style=\"color:#ffffff\"\n! style=\"background:#B11030; width:30px\"| N\u00ba\n! style=\"background:#B11030\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#B11030; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M1\n| Title = Who's Minding the Brat?\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|9|25}}\n| ShortSummary = Mindy has Mork babysit while she takes her dad to the airport.\n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M2\n| Title = The Greatest Schmoe on Earth\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|2}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M3\n| Title = To Ork or Not to Ork\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|9}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M4\n| Title = Orkan Without a Cause\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|16}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M5\n| Title = Mork Man vs. Ork Man\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|23}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M6\n| Title = Which Witch Is the Witch\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|10|30}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M7\n| Title = Every Doing Has His Day\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|11|6}}\n| ShortSummary = Mork helps Doing earn his way back in the house.\n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M8\n| Title = Beauty or the Beast\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|11|13}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M9\n| Title = Morkel and Hyde\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|11|20}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M10\n| Title = The Wimp\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|11|27}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M11\n| Title = Ride 'em Morkboy\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|12|4}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M13\n| Title = Meet Mork's Mom\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|12|11}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M14\n| Title = Muddle in the Huddle\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|12|18}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M15\n| Title = The Incredible Shrinking Mork\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1982|12|25}}\n| ShortSummary = In an effort to retrieve Mork's watch stolen from a rat, Mork, Mindy and Doing shrink using a special device.\n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M16\n| Title = The Invisible Mork\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|1|8}}\n| ShortSummary = Mork drinks strawberry juice that makes him invisible, then takes advantage of his invisibility by trying to fight a bully to win Mindy's affections.\n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M17\n| Title = The Fluke Spook\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|1|15}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M18\n| Title = Mayhem for the Mayor\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|1|22}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M19\n| Title = Coo Coo Caveboy\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|1|29}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M20\n| Title = A Treasure Ain't No Pleasure\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|2|5}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M21\n| Title = The Mork with the Midas Touch\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|2|12}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M22\n| Title = Extra Terrestrial Toddler\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|2|19}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M23\n| Title = Time Slipper Slip-Up\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1983|2|26}}\n| ShortSummary = \n| LineColor = B11030\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = M24\n| Title 